<h2>Scaling: Why Volume Matters More Than You Think</h2>
<p>Here is a number that changes the ROI conversation: businesses need <a href="/blog/how-many-blog-posts-to-rank/">a minimum of 50 to 100 published posts</a> to see meaningful organic traffic growth. Some competitive niches require 200+.</p>
<p>At 4 posts per month (the industry average), reaching 100 posts takes 25 months. At 30 posts per month with AI autoblogging, you reach 100 posts in 3.3 months.</p>
<p>That is not just faster. It is a fundamentally different competitive position.</p>
<h3>The Compounding Effect of Volume</h3>
<p><a href="/blog/blogging-statistics/">Blogging statistics</a> show that companies with 400+ published posts get 2x more traffic than those with under 200. Each article is a new entry point. Each entry point captures a different search query. The math compounds.</p>
